    "basmil_image_richtext_aJUzbg": {
      "type": "basmil-image-richtext",
      "blocks": {
        "content_thgH97": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "description": "<h3>Step 1</h3><h3>Collecting the Nectar </h3><p>Worker bees collect nectar from flowers using their long proboscis, which they store in their honey stomach (a special pouch separate from their digestive stomach).</p><h3>Step 2</h3><h3>Transporting the Nectar </h3><p>The bee returns to the hive and regurgitates the nectar into the mouth of another worker bee, transferring the nectar.</p><h3>Step 3</h3><h3>Adding the Enzymes </h3><p>The receiving bee adds enzymes to the nectar, breaking down the sugars. This process begins to transform the nectar into honey.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_6HAnJU": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image_type": "svg",
            "image_alt": "Mad Honey",
            "svg": "<svg width=\"100\" height=\"371\" viewbox=\"0 0 100 371\" fill=\"none\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\n<path d=\"M50.2614 137.894C37.183 137.894 24.6402 132.698 15.3924 123.45C6.14459 114.203 0.949219 101.66 0.949219 88.5814C0.949219 55.7066 50.2614 0.230469 50.2614 0.230469C50.2614 0.230469 99.5735 55.7066 99.5735 88.5814C99.5735 101.66 94.3782 114.203 85.1303 123.45C75.8825 132.698 63.3398 137.894 50.2614 137.894Z\" fill=\"#E8D07C\" fill-opacity=\"0.1\"></path>\n<path d=\"M50.2614 215.558C37.183 215.558 24.6402 210.362 15.3924 201.114C6.14459 191.867 0.949219 179.324 0.949219 166.245C0.949219 133.371 50.2614 77.8945 50.2614 77.8945C50.2614 77.8945 99.5735 133.371 99.5735 166.245C99.5735 179.324 94.3782 191.867 85.1303 201.114C75.8825 210.362 63.3398 215.558 50.2614 215.558Z\" fill=\"#E8D07C\" fill-opacity=\"0.3\"></path>\n<path d=\"M50.2614 293.22C37.183 293.22 24.6402 288.024 15.3924 278.777C6.14459 269.529 0.949219 256.986 0.949219 243.908C0.949219 211.033 50.2614 155.557 50.2614 155.557C50.2614 155.557 99.5735 211.033 99.5735 243.908C99.5735 256.986 94.3782 269.529 85.1303 278.777C75.8825 288.024 63.3398 293.22 50.2614 293.22Z\" fill=\"#E8D07C\" fill-opacity=\"0.6\"></path>\n<path d=\"M50.2614 370.882C37.183 370.882 24.6402 365.687 15.3924 356.439C6.14459 347.191 0.949219 334.648 0.949219 321.57C0.949219 288.695 50.2614 233.219 50.2614 233.219C50.2614 233.219 99.5735 288.695 99.5735 321.57C99.5735 334.648 94.3782 347.191 85.1303 356.439C75.8825 365.687 63.3398 370.882 50.2614 370.882Z\" fill=\"#E8D07C\"></path>\n</svg>",
            "image_width": "30%; grid-column:2/3;"
          }
        },
        "content_6jeMJd": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "description": "<h3>Step 4</h3><h3>Water Evaporation</h3><p>The bees fan their wings to create airflow inside the hive, promoting evaporation. This process thickens the nectar, reducing its water content and turning it into honey.</p><h3>Step 5</h3><h3>Storage in Cells</h3><p>Once the nectar has thickened, the bees store the honey in hexagonal beeswax cells, sealing them with a wax cap to preserve it.</p><h3>Step 6</h3><h3>Mad Honey Ripening</h3><p>The honey matures in the cells, allowing its flavor and consistency to develop. It is ready for the bees to consume or for <a href=\"/blogs/mad-honey/honey-hunting\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Mad Honey Harvesting\"><strong>mad honey harvesting</strong></a>.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
